                            ‘month of Ziv’.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Kings1-006-fn2" type="footnote">Heb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">אוּלָם </foreign>
                            ‘hall, theater, vestibule’.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Kings1-006-fn3" type="footnote">Heb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">דְּבִיר </foreign>
                            ‘inner sanctuary’.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Kings1-006-fn4" type="footnote">Heb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">לִפְנָי </foreign>
                            ‘in front of’.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Kings1-006-fn5" type="footnote">TKow.02: spelled
                                <emph>alnnynda</emph>; a scribal error.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Kings1-006-fn6" type="footnote">TKow.02: spelled <foreign
                                xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">שַרַיְינִין</foreign>
                            ; a scribal error.</note>
